; The SHAPE LANGUAGE — Pulse's foundation for saying what a value IS. One GADT type representation
; inside; plain combinators outside. From one declaration the framework derives: the codec
; (validating decode with path-collected errors), encode-side validation, normalizers, derived
; pretty-printing, and a neutral introspection [view] that downstream renderers ($jsonSchema in the
; collection lib, OpenAPI later, the admin UI later) consume without this lib knowing them.
; Deps: bson only — jsoo-safe, shared verbatim by server and browser. Methods and collections are
; disjoint consumers that WORK ON shapes; neither owns this. Unwrapped: userland says `Codec.string`.
(library
 (name fennec_pulse_codec)
 (public_name fennec.pulse.codec)
 (wrapped false)
 (libraries fennec-mongo.bson))
